      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Citizen and Society</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Daniel A Jenkins letter on neoconservatives quotes Wendell Willkie (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The neoconservatives discussed in ''When the Left Turns Right'' (Arts &amp; Ideas pages, Sept. 16) might well heed the words of Wendell Willkie. He said a liberal is someone who ''attempts to do the most difficult thing in the world -- namely, to strike a true balance between the rights of the individual and the needs of society.''</p>
        <p>DANIEL A. JENKINS  Louisville, Ky., Sept. 16, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
